Oracle ADF Developer
- ,
Date Posted: 2014/05/01 09:09:33
Ref. JB3046222
Job Description
Ability to apply technical standards, principles, theories and techniques
·
Programming using Oracle tools.
·
Translates requirements defined into logical and practical systems.
·
Participates in the architectural design, development customization and integration efforts of system development.
·
Ability to work as team with other members.
·
Possesses problem solving capabilities.
·
Excellent verbal and written communication skills.
·
Develop new applications from beginning to end within a team.
·
Maintain existing applications.
·
Write code that meets system requirements in a standards way.
·
Ensure operational procedures and documentation is updated and well maintained.
·
Analyze & troubleshoot problems and recommend solutions. Escalate as necessary.
·
Ensure Operational Procedures and Documentation are updated and well maintained.
·
Self-starter, motivated, proactive and able to learn new skills quickly
·
Has to possess good English communication skills (written as well as spoken)
·
Communicate courteously with all customers (internal and external) by telephone and email building positive relationships.
·
Attend or provide training/meetings whenever required
Skills
andidate Background Requirements:
The candidate must meet the following criteria:
·
Bsc. in Computers Science or Computer Engineering MS is a plus
·
Oracle Certified Professional (OCP) Developer track.
·
Certified in latest Oracle Application Development Framework (ADF).
·
Certified in latest Oracle Jdeveloper.
·
Six (6) years experience in IT Development environment.
·
Experience in developing applications contains oracle web applications and Oracle client server in addition to the conversion to web applications using Oracle 11g or later.
·
Experience using Oracle Application Development Framework (ADF).
·
Experience using Jdeveloper 11g.
·
Experience in dealing with Oracle Database Objects.
·
Ability to manage tasks involving Relational Databases
·
Good interpersonal, management and communication skills.
·
Must speak, read and write both English and (Arabic Natively).
·
Saudi is preferred.
